Use Raspberrypi as a wifi/3g to lan bridge using iptables
--------------------------------------------------------
Convert your Raspberry pi into a wireless network to wired LAN bridge.
That is wlan0 to eth0 or ppp0 to eth0.

Requirements
------------
For 3g USB modem to wired LAN (ppp0 to eth0)
1. sudo apt-get install ppp
2. sakis3g (included)

/etc/sakis3g.conf - configuration files for 3g modem
/usr/bin/sakis3g - sakis3g connection manager for 3g modem.
restiptables - Script to reset your current iptables
setiptables3g - enables packet forwarding between ppp0 and eth0, and also for NAT.

